PerformanceSummary.description:
Represents a workout performance summary - much of the same data as in the app, but not all.

You likely want to use the `Workout` model and `get_workouts` method instead.

performance_summary_id.description: Unique identifier for this performance summary
performance_summary_id.title: Performance Summary Id

PerformanceSummary.title: PerformanceSummary

distance.description: Distance from latitude and longitude provided to `search_studios_by_geo` method,              NULL if that method was not used
distance.title: Distance

performance_summary_id.description: The ID of the performance summary this telemetry item belongs to.
performance_summary_id.title: Performance Summary Id

zones.description: The zones associated with the telemetry.

Workout.description:
Represents a workout - combines the performance summary, data from the new bookings endpoint, and telemetry data.

The final product contains all the performance summary data, the detailed data over time, as well as the class,
coach, studio, and rating data from the new endpoint.

This should match the data that is shown in the OTF app after a workout.

performance_summary_id.description: Unique identifier for this performance summary
performance_summary_id.title: Performance Summary Id

booking_id.description: The booking id for the new bookings endpoint.
booking_id.title: Booking Id

class_uuid.description: Used by the ratings endpoint - seems to fall off after a few months
class_uuid.title: Class Uuid

Workout.title: Workout
